# Alouma Web direction

Alouma Web is the browser version of the existing Alouma iOS CV builder.

The goal is not to invent a new product. The goal is to port the existing product logic, rendering philosophy, and recruiter-grade CV output into a web-first implementation.

## Product principles

- Alouma helps users build a clear, recruiter-readable CV through guided structure.
- The product must feel calm, premium, editorial, and practical.
- Output quality matters more than visual novelty.
- The exported CV/PDF is the source of truth for user trust.
- Users should stay in control. AI suggestions are previews, never automatic overwrites.
- Avoid generic AI resume-builder language and generic SaaS patterns.

## Migration principles

- Preserve proven iOS product decisions unless explicitly asked to change them.
- Port product logic before inventing new features.
- Keep the web repo clean and modular.
- Treat migration docs in `docs/migration/` as authoritative context.
- Do not assume iOS docs are current if the code/audit says otherwise.
- Do not rewrite the iOS app from this repo.
